h1 Intelligence

h1 Bonuses / modifiers

p Intelligence provides a modifier to the following actions:
  ul
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Abilities-and-Spellcasters'>Bonus Spells</a>: PCs who use intelligence as their primary casting stat (such as Wizards), gain additional spells / day based on their intelligence.
    li <a href='/skills/'>Skill Points</a>: PCs gain skill points for each level. The intelligence modifier is used for awarding additional skill points.
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/linguistics'>Bonus Starting Languages</a>: a character with high intelligence starts with a number of additional languages equal to their modifier. Note that negatives do not reduce the number of languages.
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/appraise'>Appraise skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/craft'>Craft skill</a>: note that Craft has several separate sub-types that are trained individually. Examples include: <i>armor</i>, <i>glass</i>, <i>traps</i>.
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge'>Knowledge skill</a>: note that Knowledge has several separate sub-types that are trained individually. Examples include: <i>arcana</i>, <i>history</i>, <i>religion</i>.
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/linguistics'>Linguistics skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/spellcraft'>Spellcraft skill</a>

h1 Improving your Intelligence

p There are several avenues for improving this ability. The abilities within a category do not stack. You cannot have two enhancement bonuses active at once, only the largest bonus takes effect.

p In general, magical items are the easiest way to start boosting your stats.

p Note that every two points of ability improvement provides a one point modifier to the relevant abilities listed above.

h2 Racial bonuses

p The following races receive racial bonsues to their intelligence.

ul
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/human">Human</a>, <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/half-elf">Half-elf</a>, <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/half-orc">Half-orc</a> (<i>must pick this bonus</i>)
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/elf">Elf</a>

h2 Enhancment bonuses

p The following items and spells provide an enhancement bonus. Generally the highest enhancement bonus available is +6.

ul
  li <b>Spell</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/f/fox-s-cunning">Fox's Cunning</a> (<span class="magic_items_bonus">+4</span>)
  li <b>Scroll</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/f/fox-s-cunning">Fox's Cunning</a> scroll.
    mixin magic_item_table_vertical([4],[150],["3 min duration (<i>add 50 gp for each additional min</i>)"])
  li <b>Potion</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/f/fox-s-cunning">Fox's Cunning</a> potion
    mixin magic_item_table_vertical([4],[300],["3 min duration (<i>add 100 gp for each additional min</i>)"])
  li <b>Wand</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/f/fox-s-cunning">Fox's Cunning</a> wand
    mixin magic_item_table_vertical([4],[4500],["3 min duration (<i>add 1500 gp for each additional min</i>)"])
  li <b>Magical Belts</b>:
    ul
      li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/h-l/headband-of-vast-intelligence">Headband of Vast Intelligence</a>
        mixin magic_item_table([2,4,6],[4000,16000,36000])
      li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/h-l/headband-of-mental-prowess">Headband of Mental Prowess</a><br />This headband improves two mental stats, so two of Int, Wis and Cha
        mixin magic_item_table([2,4,6],[10000,40000,90000])
      li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/h-l/headband-of-mental-superiority">Headband of Mental Superiority</a><br />This headband improves all three mental attribute (Int, Wis AND Cha)
        mixin magic_item_table([2,4,6],[16000,64000,144000])

h2 Inherent bonuses

ul
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/a-b/book-tome-of-clear-thought">Tome of Clear Thought</a>, magical item.
    mixin magic_item_table([1,2,3,4,5],[27500,55000,82500,110000,137500])
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer">Sorcerer Bloodlines</a>: some sorcerer bloodlines provide inherent bonuses to a particular stat. One example of this would be the <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer/bloodlines/bloodlines-from-paizo/abyssal-bloodline">Abyssal Bloodline</a>.


h2 Untyped bonuses

p The untyped bonus is in a category of its own and stacks with all other bonuses.

ul
  li <b>Level bonus</b><br />Every fourth level (4, 8, 12, 16, 20), the character can increase one stat by one point. <i>Note that this is only 1 point, stats typically need to be increased by two points to improve relevant abilities.</i>

